{"title":"Spotlight: Lezyne Strip Drive Pro rear light review","link":"https://cyclingtips.com/2021/03/spotlight-lezyne-strip-drive-pro-rear-light-review/","date":1615766460000,"content":"<p><em><a href=\"https://cyclingtips.com/tag/spotlight/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Spotlight</a>&nbsp;is a new series on CyclingTips that we’re using to briefly showcase new products we’ve just received, and/or products that require just a short review. This regular and short-form tech coverage replaces our previous&nbsp;<a href=\"https://cyclingtips.com/tag/tech-round-up/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Tech Round-Up series</a>.</em>&nbsp;<em>Be sure to check out all the photos in the sliding gallery above.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<p>I’m a long-time believer in riding with <a href=\"https://cyclingtips.com/2017/02/see-seen-every-cyclist-needs-know-daytime-running-lights/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">day-time-running lights</a>, and given they&#8217;re a safety-related product, I’m constantly on the hunt for something better. I recently bought myself the Lezyne Strip Drive Pro, a mid-priced rear light that’s the equal-brightest option in the company’s extensive range. It’s impressed me enough that I thought I’d share it. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Lezyne claims the Strip Drive Pro offers a peak output of 300 lumens, and while I don’t have the measuring equipment to confirm this, I can confirm that the five LEDs pack a punch that can be seen from a long way away (and with surprisingly good side visibility, too). My usual go-to rear light is a <a href=\"https://cyclingtips.com/2016/12/ten-products-i-loved-in-2016-david-rome/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">previous-generation Bontrager Flare R</a>, and the Lezyne Strip Drive Pro is noticeably more blinding to look at.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In its brightest day-flashing mode the light is claimed to last for just three hours, while less-bright settings will go noticeably longer. There are a total of 11 modes, and while that feels like too many when you’re clicking through them, the light thankfully remembers and reverts to the mode you last used.   </p>\n\n\n\n<p>First released in 2019, the Strip Drive Pro recently received a small refinement that moved it from an integrated USB stick to a more traditional cable-based Micro USB port for charging. This port is sealed by a large rubber cap that provides a robust seal and a reassuring “pop” when opening. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Most often it&#8217;s the mounting bracket that lets down otherwise good lights, but thankfully Lezyne has kept things simple with a strong co-moulded build that’s held in place with a replaceable band strap (an 0-ring could be used, too). The light angle is fixed and, strapped in place, it retains a narrow 36 mm profile that avoids leg rub.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The rubber backing is flexible and deep, shaped to handle both skinny aero seatposts and regular round posts, and included is a rubber chock/wedge for use on flat-backed seatposts (D-shaped). In my experience, the light fits best with seatpost shapes that don’t require this wedge. There is no angle adjustment available.   </p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Lezyne also offers this light with an “Alert” feature which uses an accelerometer to brighten the light upon sudden braking. This feature adds US$5 / AU$10.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Weight:</strong> 62 g (with mounting strap)<br><strong>Price:</strong> US$55 / AU$90<br><strong>More info:</strong> <a href=\"https://ride.lezyne.com/collections/led-lights-rear/products/strip-drive-pro\">ride.lezyne.com</a>&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-3 is-cropped wp-block-gallery__slider\"><ul class=\"blocks-gallery-grid\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"754\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-9-1340x754.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"490060\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-9.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/?attachment_id=490060\" class=\"wp-image-490060\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-9-1340x754.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-9-650x366.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-9-190x107.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-9-1080x608.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-9-16x9.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-9.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">There are 11 different flashing and continuous light modes to make varying use of the five inline LEDs.</figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"754\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-6-1340x754.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"490054\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-6.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/?attachment_id=490054\" class=\"wp-image-490054\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-6-1340x754.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-6-650x366.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-6-190x107.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-6-1080x608.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-6-16x9.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-6.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">The Lezyne Strip Drive Pro (v2) is pictured here on a 2021 Giant TCR Advanced Pro seatpost. </figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"754\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-7-1340x754.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"490056\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-7.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/?attachment_id=490056\" class=\"wp-image-490056\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-7-1340x754.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-7-650x366.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-7-190x107.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-7-1080x608.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-7-16x9.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-7.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">The Strip Drive Pro is 78 mm in length and 36 mm at its widest. </figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"754\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-8-1340x754.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"490059\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-8.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/?attachment_id=490059\" class=\"wp-image-490059\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-8-1340x754.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-8-650x366.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-8-190x107.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-8-1080x608.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-8-16x9.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-8.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">Lezyne claims that the Strip Drive Pro offers 270º of visibility. It&#8217;s certainly the brightest square-on, but it provides plenty of side-on visibility too. </figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"754\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-2-1340x754.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"490044\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-2.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/?attachment_id=490044\" class=\"wp-image-490044\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-2-1340x754.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-2-650x366.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-2-190x107.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-2-1080x608.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-2-16x9.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-2.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">Lezyne has kept the mounting system quite simple, and I like that. </figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"754\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-3-1340x754.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"490047\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-3.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/?attachment_id=490047\" class=\"wp-image-490047\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-3-1340x754.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-3-650x366.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-3-190x107.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-3-1080x608.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-3-16x9.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-3.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">The light&#8217;s co-moulded rubber backing is shaped to work with a variety of seatposts. </figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"754\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-4-1340x754.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"490048\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-4.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/?attachment_id=490048\" class=\"wp-image-490048\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-4-1340x754.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-4-650x366.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-4-190x107.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-4-1080x608.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-4-16x9.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-4.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">The large rubber plug consumes the base of the light and offers a tight fit. </figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"754\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-5-1340x754.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"490051\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-5.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/?attachment_id=490051\" class=\"wp-image-490051\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-5-1340x754.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-5-650x366.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-5-190x107.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-5-1080x608.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-5-16x9.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-5.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">The button offers a tactile feel and is well sealed from the elements. </figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"754\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-1-1340x754.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"490041\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-1.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/?attachment_id=490041\" class=\"wp-image-490041\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-1-1340x754.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-1-650x366.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-1-190x107.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-1-1080x608.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-1-16x9.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lezyne-Strip-Drive-Pro-v2-rear-light-review-cyclingtips-2021-1.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">There is a small LED indicator for battery life. </figcaption></figure></li></ul></figure>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://cyclingtips.com/2021/03/spotlight-lezyne-strip-drive-pro-rear-light-review/\">Spotlight: Lezyne Strip Drive Pro rear light review</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://cyclingtips.com\">CyclingTips</a>.</p>","author":"Dave Rome","siteTitle":"CyclingTips","siteHash":"30feca30fb3902119bf2da6559e7337232527b61c9abe0a00f5d7543c6aa6c84","entryHash":"1ad23d21d573d77af01980ce5115ed940760e187b4cf8556c5abf54be07f58b3","category":"Cycling"}